public static boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
    if (n < 0) {
        return false;
    }
    else if (n == 1) {
        return false;
    }
    else if (n == 2) {
        return true;
    }
    else {
        return (n > 1 && isPowerOfThree(n - 1));
    }
}
```

This function recursively checks if the remainder of dividing the number by 3 is 0. If the remainder is not 0, the number cannot be a power of 3. If the remainder is 0, the number is a power of 3. If the number is 1, it is not a power of 3. If the number is 2, it is a power of 3.

